'''Movima''' is a language that is spoken by about 1,400 (nearly half) of the Movima, a group of Native Americans that resides in the [[Llanos de Moxos]] region of the [[Bolivia]]n Amazon, in northeastern Bolivia. It is considered a [[language isolate]], as it has not been proven to be related to any other language.

